Kano State Hisbah Board has arrested 53 teenagers for alleged involvement in immoral acts in Kano city. Malam Lawal Ibrahim, the board’s spokesman, in a statement in Kano said they were arrested following a tip-off. He said the suspects were apprehended on Tuesday night at Lamido Crescent in Nassarawa Local Government for selling hard drugs and intoxicant. “The suspects comprise 27 boys and 26 girls, all of whom are between the ages of 17 and 19. “Our men went there around 10pm and arrested 53 suspects,” Ibrahim said.